3.00	Light_second	Light-second	A light-second is a unit of length useful in astronomy, telecommunications and relativistic physics. It is defined as the distance that light travels in free space in one second, and is equal to exactly 299,792,458 metres. It is just over 186,000 miles and almost 109 feet.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/1e13m_comparison_Hale_Bopp_and_smaller_-_HQ_no_transparency.png/150px-1e13m_comparison_Hale_Bopp_and_smaller_-_HQ_no_transparency.png
